# =============================================================================
# .trivyignore - Trivy False Positive Suppressions
# Book Reference: Chapter 3, Section 3.3.2.4 - Example 3.10
# =============================================================================
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file to your repository root as .trivyignore
#   2. Replace example entries with your actual suppressions
#   3. Every entry MUST have: reason, expiry date, and ticket reference
#   4. Run quarterly review to remove expired entries
#   5. Require security team approval for new entries via code review
#
# FORMAT:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # reason | expires: YYYY-MM-DD | ticket: TICKET-ID
#
# REVIEW SCHEDULE:
#   Next review due: [DATE]
#   Reviewer: [NAME]
#   Last reviewed: [DATE]
# =============================================================================

# =============================================================================
# Category 1: Not exploitable in our codebase
# The vulnerable code path is never called
# =============================================================================

# CVE-2023-12345  # Not exploitable: vulnerable function xml.parseString() is
#                 # never called. We only use xml.parse() which is unaffected.
#                 # Verified by code search 2024-01-15.
#                 # expires: 2024-07-01 | ticket: SEC-123

# =============================================================================
# Category 2: Mitigated by compensating control
# A WAF, network policy, or other control prevents exploitation
# =============================================================================

# CVE-2023-67890  # Mitigated: WAF rule WAF-RULE-456 blocks the HTTP request
#                 # pattern required for exploitation. Rule verified active
#                 # in all environments on 2024-01-10.
#                 # expires: 2024-04-01 | ticket: SEC-124

# =============================================================================
# Category 3: No fix available
# Vendor has not released a patch - short expiry, check frequently
# =============================================================================

# CVE-2023-99999  # No fix available as of 2024-01-15. Upstream issue tracked
#                 # at https://github.com/vendor/package/issues/999.
#                 # Internal network only, not exposed to untrusted input.
#                 # expires: 2024-02-15 | ticket: SEC-125

# =============================================================================
# Category 4: Accepted risk (requires security team written approval)
# =============================================================================

# CVE-2022-88888  # Accepted risk: CVSS 3.1 score 4.2 (Medium). Requires
#                 # physical access to exploit. Not applicable to our
#                 # cloud-hosted deployment model.
#                 # Approved by: security-lead@company.com on 2024-01-01
#                 # expires: 2024-07-01 | ticket: SEC-126
